<div class="kksr-legend" style="font-size: 19.2px;">
            5/5 - (1 vote)    </div>
    </div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It’s up to you to decide when’s the best time to travel to Costa Rica with your children. It’s </span><b>one of the most important tourist destinations in the Americas,</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and one of the safest countries for a peaceful family holiday. </span><b>A country you’ll fall in love with thanks to its incredible natural riches</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, the warmth of its people and an enviable </span><a href="https://www.govisitcostarica.co.cr/travelInfo/weather.asp" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">tropical climate</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>
<div id="toc_container" class="toc_light_blue no_bullets"><p class="toc_title">Contenido</p><ul class="toc_list"><li></li><li><ul><li></li><li></li><li></li></ul></li></ul></div>
<h2><span id="When_is_the_best_time_to_travel_to_Costa_Rica_with_children">When is the best time to travel to Costa Rica with children?</span></h2>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21183" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201920%201080'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="1920" height="1080" title="" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Principal-8.jpg 1920w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Principal-8-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Principal-8-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Principal-8-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Principal-8-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Principal-8.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21183" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Principal-8.jpg" alt="" width="1920" height="1080" title="" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Principal-8.jpg 1920w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Principal-8-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Principal-8-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Principal-8-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Principal-8-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px" /></noscript></p>
<p><b>Costa Rica is a good place to we travel with children throughout the year</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. It’s a country which experiences stable and pleasant temperatures within the parameters of a tropical climate. There are two distinct seasons: a dry season (summer), and a rainy season (winter).</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><b>The dry season is from December to April.</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> These are the months with the highest temperatures, between 25 and 30 °C, although there are differences between the different areas of the country. Perfect for the kids to enjoy a vacation without extremes of temperature.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><b>The rainy season, between May and November, is for many is the perfect season for the kids to enjoy all the natural splendours of Costa Rica.</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> It’s cooler and more humid.</span></p>
<h2><span id="Not_sure_what_to_do_in_Costa_Rica_if_youre_travelling_with_children">Not sure what to do in Costa Rica if you’re travelling with children?</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Costa Rica is a country that </span><b>offers an incredible variety of options for children to enjoy an amazing holiday.</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> It’s the ideal country for whatever type of activities you prefer, as there is a huge variety of options.</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20494" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/2-08.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/2-08-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/2-08-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/2-08-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/2-08-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/2-08.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20494" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/2-08.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/2-08.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/2-08-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/2-08-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/2-08-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/2-08-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Costa Rica is the ideal natural paradise where the kids can live out incredible adventures in a unique natural environment, in a country packed with history where they can visit towns and cities, check out the museums and, of course, enjoy its magnificent beaches.</span></p>
<h3><span id="National_Parks">National Parks</span></h3>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20498" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/catarata-de-La-Paz-06.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/catarata-de-La-Paz-06-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/catarata-de-La-Paz-06-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/catarata-de-La-Paz-06-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/catarata-de-La-Paz-06-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/catarata-de-La-Paz-06.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20498" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/catarata-de-La-Paz-06.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/catarata-de-La-Paz-06.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/catarata-de-La-Paz-06-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/catarata-de-La-Paz-06-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/catarata-de-La-Paz-06-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/catarata-de-La-Paz-06-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the strengths of Costa Rican tourism is its impressive </span><a href="https://www.govisitcostarica.co.cr/travelInfo/nationalParks.asp" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">national parks</span></a> <span style="font-weight: 400;">. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Incredible protected natural spaces that are clean and well conserved, where your children can enjoy that direct contact with the natural world.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><b>In the La Paz Natural Park you’ll find the famous La Paz waterfall</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. It has a huge variety of animals: pumas, toucans, monkeys, hummingbirds, and snakes, among others. A perfect environment for the kids to get to know animals up close and personal, but of course with all the necessary safety measures in place. They </span><b>can also enjoy incredible adventures such as crossing the jungle on zip lines, or rafting with the whole family.</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20502" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Monos-03.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Monos-03-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Monos-03-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Monos-03-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Monos-03-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Monos-03.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20502" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Monos-03.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Monos-03.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Monos-03-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Monos-03-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Monos-03-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Monos-03-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></p>
<p><b>The Manuel Antonio National Park is the one most frequently visited in the country.</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> A protected natural area with a great biodiversity that also has beautiful beaches</span><b>. Beaches where, as well as the joys of sea and sand, the kids can amuse themselves with the pranks of the animals that live there</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, such as monkeys.</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20508" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Volcán-Irazú-02.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Volcán-Irazú-02-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Volcán-Irazú-02-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Volcán-Irazú-02-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Volcán-Irazú-02-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Volcán-Irazú-02.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20508" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Volcán-Irazú-02.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Volcán-Irazú-02.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Volcán-Irazú-02-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Volcán-Irazú-02-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Volcán-Irazú-02-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Volcán-Irazú-02-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></p>
<p><b>Your kids can visit a real volcano.</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> You can visit the </span><b>Irazú Volcano National Park,</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> home to </span><b>the highest volcano in Costa Rica</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. It’s an active volcano, and there’s a kilometre-wide lake of volcanic origin with amazing turquoise waters in the main crater. An experience they will never forget.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3><span id="Enjoy_the_Costa_Rican_beaches">Enjoy the Costa Rican beaches</span></h3>
<p><b>Costa Rica’s beaches are another of the wonders that this beautiful country offers for </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">the family to enjoy.</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20506" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Surf-07.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Surf-07-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Surf-07-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Surf-07-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Surf-07-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Surf-07.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20506" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Surf-07.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Surf-07.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Surf-07-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Surf-07-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Surf-07-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Surf-07-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Santa Teresa beach in Puntarenas is one not to be missed. One of the best, where </span><b>your kids can have surfing lessons and enjoy delicious local fruit</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and cool slushies made with natural juices.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><b>The islands of the Santa Catalina archipelago are perfect for children to get know the wonders of the local marine inhabitants</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">: sharks, manta rays and fish of every colour imaginable.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20500" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Guanacaste-05.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Guanacaste-05-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Guanacaste-05-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Guanacaste-05-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Guanacaste-05-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Guanacaste-05.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20500" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Guanacaste-05.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Guanacaste-05.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Guanacaste-05-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Guanacaste-05-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Guanacaste-05-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Guanacaste-05-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></p>
<p><a href="https://www.govisitcostarica.co.cr/region/guanacaste/guanacaste.asp" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The beaches</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> of Guanacaste</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">are extremely popular. There, you can do lots of family activities, such as surfing, sport fishing or diving. </span><b>Beautiful beaches where you can see turtles and enjoy perfectly conserved and protected natural environments.</b></p>
<h3><span id="Costa_Rica_fun_and_interesting_facts">Costa Rica: fun and interesting facts</span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">And to get kids excited about the trip, try telling them about </span><b>Costa Rica and its oddities:</b><b><br />
</b><b><br />
</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">The country has one of the five </span><a href="https://cenie.eu/es/blog/zonas-azules-los-paraisos-de-la-longevidad" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Blue Zones</span></a> <span style="font-weight: 400;">in the world: Nicoya Where many of the inhabitants maintain an active life and live for over 100 years.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span></p>
<p><b>Costa Rica contains 5% of the world&#8217;s biodiversity.</b></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20496" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Biodiversidad-04.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Biodiversidad-04-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Biodiversidad-04-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Biodiversidad-04-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Biodiversidad-04-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Biodiversidad-04.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20496" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Biodiversidad-04.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Biodiversidad-04.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Biodiversidad-04-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Biodiversidad-04-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Biodiversidad-04-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Biodiversidad-04-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript><b>It’s considered one of the happiest nations in the world</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Without a doubt, the </span><b>best time to travel to Costa Rica</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> with children is whenever is good for you. The most important thing is to get them involved in preparing for the trip, listen to their expectations and take them into account when you’re planning activities. Costa Rica is a country that opens its arms to you and </span><b>gives you the opportunity to enjoy an unforgettable family holiday</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
		</div>

